Sazka AS, a bankrupt Czech lottery
company, repaid 567 million koruna ($30.2 million) to  Bank of
New York Mellon Corp. (BK) , one of its creditors,  Pravo  reported,
citing Lenka Ticha, spokeswoman for Sazkaâ€™s administrator.  Sazka, based in  Prague , raised the cash for the repayment
by selling assets, the newspaper said. The company can now start
repayments to other creditors, Pravo said, citing Jan Cupka, the
